<h1 id="select2">Select2</h1>
<p><a href="https://travis-ci.org/select2/select2"><img src="https://travis-ci.org/select2/select2.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status"></a></p>
<p>Select2 is a jQuery-based replacement for select boxes. It supports searching,<br>remote data sets, and pagination of results.</p>
<p>To get started, checkout examples and documentation at<br><a href="https://select2.github.io/">https://select2.github.io/</a></p>
<h2 id="use%20cases">Use cases</h2>
<ul>
<li>Enhancing native selects with search.</li>
<li>Enhancing native selects with a better multi-select interface.</li>
<li>Loading data from JavaScript: easily load items via AJAX and have them<br>searchable.</li>
<li>Nesting optgroups: native selects only support one level of nesting. Select2<br>does not have this restriction.</li>
<li>Tagging: ability to add new items on the fly.</li>
<li>Working with large, remote datasets: ability to partially load a dataset based<br>on the search term.</li>
<li>Paging of large datasets: easy support for loading more pages when the results<br>are scrolled to the end.</li>
<li>Templating: support for custom rendering of results and selections.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="browser%20compatibility">Browser compatibility</h2>
<ul>
<li>IE 8+</li>
<li>Chrome 8+</li>
<li>Firefox 10+</li>
<li>Safari 3+</li>
<li>Opera 10.6+</li>
</ul>
